<h3>Question 8</h3>
<div><p><p>Explain cloud computing in brief.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>Cloud computing is the general term for anything that involves delivering hosted services over the internet. It is the use of the computing resouces i.e hardware and software that are delivered as a service over a network typically over internet. Its the on-demand availability ofcomputer system resource especially data storage and computing power, without direct active management by the user.</p>
<p>Characteristics of cloud computing are:</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>On-demand self-service :Cloud computing can help us to achieve server time and network storage as per demand without human interaction with each service provider.</li>
<li>Resource pooling : The provider&#8217;s computing resource is pooled to provide service to multiple user using different model  with different physical and virtual resource dynamically as per the user need.</li>
<li>Rapid elasticity: To the consumer, the capabilities avilable for provisining often appear to be unlimited.</li>
<li>Broad network access: Capabilities are available over the network and they can be accessed using different mechanism.</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The benefits of cloud computing are:</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Flexibility: Users can access cloud services from anywhere with an internet connection as needed.</li>
<li>Efficiency :  New applications can rapidly get into production.</li>
<li>Enhanced strategic value: Cloud computing enables organizations to use various technologies and the most up-to-date innovations to gain a competitive edge.</li>
<li>Cost effective: Cloud computing lets you offload some or all of the expense and effort of purchasing, installing, configuring and managing.</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<h3>Question 9</h3>
<div><p><p>What is data warehouse? Explain.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>Data Warehouse emphasize on the means to retrieve ans analyse data, to extracct, transform and load data. It is a process of centralization of the data management and retrieval. Centralization is needed to maximize the useraccess and analysis.It is integrated generally at the organization level, by combining data from different databases. A Data Warehouseis considered as separate from DBMS, it stores a huge amount of data, which is typically collected from multiple heterogeneous sources like files, DBMS, etc. It may contain multiple databases, within each database, data is organized into tables and columns. An ordinary Database can store MBs to GBs of data and that too for a specific purpose. For storing data of TB size, the storage shifted to the Data Warehouse.</p>
<p>The primary goals of the data warehouse are the following:</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Provide access to the data of management;</li>
<li>Data consistncy;</li>
<li>Capacity to seperate and combine data;</li>
<li>Drive business re-engineering;</li>
<li>Publish used data.</li>
</ul>
<p>Benefits of a data warehouse include the following:</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Informed decision making;</li>
<li>Consolidated data from many sources;</li>
<li>Historical data analysis;</li>
<li>Data quality, consistency, and accuracy;</li>
<li>Separation of analytics processing from transactional databases, which improves performance of both systems.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Data Warehouse</strong> is subject oriented, integrated, time varient and non-volatile collection of data in support of management&#8217;s decision making process. Data from data warehouse are never updated or deleted hence it is called non-volatile. Data from different sources are incorporated in the data warehouse so it is called integrated.</p>
</div>
<h3>Question 10</h3>
<div><p><p>What are different element of multimedia?</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>Multimedia is a combination of different media such as text, audio, video, graphics, and animation.</p>
<p><strong>Text:</strong> The text is the most basic one and is used in delivering information itself. It is used to describe or explain things briefly.</p>
<p><strong>Audio:</strong> Sound, music, and voice constitute the element of audio. It is used for delivering instructions, background music, or commentaries so as to make things more interesting</p>
<p><strong>Video:</strong> Video is a powerful multimedia element that couples sound and pictures to deliver motion. It is helpful in demonstration, tutorial, or voice-over.</p>
<p><strong>Graphics:</strong> Graphics are photos or drawings supporting the content. They are made up of snapshots, diagrams, and graphs, which render the presentation interesting.</p>
<p><strong>Animation:</strong> Animation is moving figures or objects. Animation helps demonstrate things that can hardly be recreated in actual form, e.g., scientific experiments.</p>
<p>All these elements come together to create interactive and engaging multimedia products like games, presentations, and learning applications.</p>
</div>
<h3>Question 11</h3>
<div><p><p>Explain security awareness and security policy in brief.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>Security awareness is the knowledge and attitude of an individual or an organization regarding the protection of their assets from security threats, risks, and vulnerabilities. It is the knowledge and attitudes of members of a group that is tasked with the protection of the physical, and more important, informational assets of a specific organization. It refers to the understanding that there exists the potential for both deliberate and accidental action that could steal, damage, or misuse the data stored within a computer system. It includes programs to educate employees about common threats.</p>
<p>A security policy also known as an information security policy or IT security policy specifies the rules, expectations, and overall approach that an organization adopts to safeguard the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of its data. It is a written document in an organization outlining how to protect the organization from threats, including computer security threats, and how to handle situations when they do occur. Security policies are aimed at protecting a company&#8217;s physical assets, such as buildings and equipment, including computers and other IT equipment. They protect intellectual property from costly events, like data breaches and data leaks. They provides benifits like guard reputation, dictate the role of employees, identify the third parties vulnerabilities and protect valuable assets.</p>
</div>
<h3>Question 12</h3>
<div><p><p>Write short notes on:</p>
<ol>
<li>Cache memory</li>
<li>IoT</li>
</ol</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><h1><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">a.</span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"> Cache memory</span></span></strong></h1>
<p>The speed of CPU  is extremely high compared to the access time of main memory. Therefore the performance of CPU decreases due to the slow speed of main memory so to decreases mismatch in operating speed a small memory chip is attached between CPU and main memory which is called cache memory. Cache is used by the CPU for memory which is being accessed over and over again. Instead of pulling it every time from the main memory, it is put in cache for fast access. It is also a smaller memory, however, larger than internal register. It is a small amount of high-speed memory that lies between the CPU’s and the main memory which is used to improves the processing speed of CPU’s by storing frequently used data and instruction. As the microprocessor processes data, it looks first in the cache memory and if it finds the data there (from a previous reading of data), it does not have to do the more time-consuming reading of data from larger memory. These memories are very expensive as have bigger size of cache memory hence its size is normally kept small.</p>
<h1><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">b. <span style="text-decoration: underline;">IoT</span></span></strong></h1>
<p>IOT stands for Internet of Things. It is system of interrelated computing devices, mechanical and digital machines, objects, animals or people that provided with unique identifiers and ability to transfer data over a network.</p>
<p>Over a past few years, IOT has become most popular technology. With the help of these, we can connect with every objects such as kitchen appliances, car, thermostat, baby monitors and many more.</p>
<p>The major advantage of IOT are</p>
<ol style="list-style-type:decimal;">
<li>Monitor</li>
<li>Accessibility</li>
<li>Speed</li>
<li>Better Time management</li>
</ol>
<p>The disadvantage of IOT are</p>
<ol style="list-style-type:decimal;">
<li>Data Breach</li>
<li>Dependence</li>
<li>Complexity</li>
<li>Privacy Issue</li>
</ol>
</div>
